Operation in Afghanistan
Originally, the Luftwaffe has published the videos with the aim of recruiting soldiers, and, as the Ministry of Defence says, the contributions also serve the purpose of informing the population about the actual objectives of foreign missions.
Propaganda, published in this way, is almost free of charge compared to traditional television advertising, says defense expert Gordon Mackenzie to the BBC, but these videos always carry a certain amount of political message in them, as they confirm the existence of the military measures decided by the government in their own way.
America’s Recruit With Game
