Political Capital: Hungarian Guard increases State risk
According to the Political Capital Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysis Division), the activities of the Hungarian Guards founded this August with the support of the "movement for a better Hungary" have increased the risk of Hungary and the region in several ways.
Among other things, the Institute's "risk warning report" states: In connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guards, the highest political risk is the "distorting of the already existing ethnic tensions between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy populations in Hungary, which could even lead to violent ethnic conflicts in the short term".
The main reason for this is the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is probably aimed at provocation of such an argument, according to the research institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure on the part of the political leaders: "People of public life have left the discussion of the Roma question to representatives of radical political groups who have now built their political strategy on Roma-Hungary counterparts".
It is believed that this would aggravate the problem, make reasonable dialogue impossible, favour extremities, and increase the likelihood of violent conflicts.
The research institute also believes that the activities of the Hungarian Guard, not least thanks to the enormous attention of the local and foreign media, "has seriously damaged Hungary's image abroad, especially in terms of confidence in stability and democratic maturity".
We remember: Since autumn 2006, the reorganisation of radical and extremely right-wing groups in Hungary has been constantly on the rise, so that since summer 2007, several "national self-defense associations" have been formed.
"These groups mean that they define themselves as civil organizations, while openly bragging to prepare their members for - including armed - defence tasks (catastrophy, national defence, order-keeping), calling for the inappropriateness of the police, the army, or the state itself," it said.
And further, this is all done in accordance with that method, which tries to embrace different political and political aspirations as a bourgeois initiative based on the political and party demise of the population.
The emphasis of the civil character and the form of association thus serve not only the circumvention of legal hurdles that might arise in the course of registration in court - it is at the same time a political strategy.
As the analysis shows, the activities of the Hungarian Guard constitute a risk-enhancing factor for relations with neighbouring countries.
"In recent months, the Hungarian Guard has been cited as a potential source of danger in several neighbouring states, so some ultra-nationalist politicians of certain neighbouring countries see the establishment of the Hungarian Guard as confirmation of their own anti-Hungary policy.
All this has an impact on the political stability of the region" - it was said.
From the point of view of the research institute, the establishment of the Hungarian Guard is not a single phenomenon in Central and Eastern Europe, so the political risk for the entire region has increased.
As reported, the activities of the Hungarian Guards are comparable to those of the Bulgarian National Guards, whose foundation was announced by the far-right Bulgarian National Union (BNU) in August 2007.
In the background of the creation of the Bulgarian Guard, there were the Roma masquerades that took place in a district of Sofia (Krasna Poljana).
