The Congress agrees with the MIFID Directive, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel with the parliamentary elaboration, which today ended its session with the Senate Congress Decision on the supplementary/amending applications to the project, the government published the provisions arising from the new law, with the intention of enabling the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the Congress and Senate members who had pursued in their negotiations and votes the aim of establishing the best possible regime that guarantees investor security and regulates the individual entrepreneurial activities in order to guarantee a generally efficient market situation.
In addition to the modernisation of the financial markets, MIFID, which is re-established by the Securities Services Regulation, is pursuing an improvement in investor protection, an increase in the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) control claim and the promotion of cooperation between the various control authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive enables specialised companies as well as natural or legal persons to provide financial advice and also contributes to the establishment of new financial services companies (ESIS), the advisory companies that join together with investment and brokerage companies of securities.
In addition, it extends the number of financial transaction management systems, adding the multilateral securities trading systems and systems to internationalise trade orders, which would eventually compete with current economic operators.
The law obliges investment companies to notify the priorities of their corporate profile, the confrontation and the forms of dealing with risks on the market and to register all the projects carried out in order to facilitate the CNMV’s control task.
The Congress Economic Commission subsequently made further changes, with the decision that the debt securities provided with titles must now be considered as complex financial resources for the investor due to their high risk level, confirmed by the US mortgage and banking crisis. (US mortgage crisis)
In addition, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal limitation of the working areas of certified economic scientists was used; 30 years after 1977 the Regulation, which restricted the areas of work reserved for economic scientists, was adopted.
The Senate, for its part, established new positions in the financial sector, such as those of the economic mediator working on foreign invoices, does not require authorisation from CNMV and can offer its services for the commercialisation of products and for the acquisition of customers at the same time several investment companies.
