Which insurance is best suited for me?
The car insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the height of which depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of the creation of the driver's license, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you have to be clear about what we're dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance undertaking.
This agreement is held in writing by means of an insurance contract, which states that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and is obliged, in return, to submit the corresponding amount of the settlement in case of damages.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance that consists of several factors, including age, gender, time of creation of a driving licence, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to statistics, so that higher contributions are also due in the event of a higher risk of accident.
For this reason, both over 25 years of age and women have to make less contribution payments, as statistics show that thanks to their caution, these groups have a lower accident rate.
The same applies also to married persons, as according to statistical values and thus also after the conviction of the companies, they tend to be less accidents than individuals alone.
The benefit to be gained from the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus also the probability of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance must take into account a whole range of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
We now list at this point the most important points that should be considered in the selection of an insurance in order not only to be able to make a performance-oriented, but also a price-oriented choice.
The under 25-year-olds face numerous obstacles when choosing low-cost insurance, such as low driving practices and the young driver's license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to complete a full cash insurance scheme, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The careful drivers can choose a full-cash kit with self-participation, so that the services of a full-cash insurance are covered, but are offered at a low price.
This type of contract means that the customer must pay part of the amount caused by the damage itself.
The amount is fixed before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium , which is higher the lower the amount to be paid , Luis Noguera, Spain's main representative at First Europe, a intermediary for online insurance .
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not the damage caused by the car itself.
Moreover, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's a piece of advice.
When you are under 25 years of age, it is in your hand to reduce insurance costs; so your credit increase by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate for the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in said tariffs.
The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its earnings.
If the company has a high yield year behind it, it may be possible to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it is most useful to opt for full-time self-interest insurance.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been removed.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to complete a full insurance scheme; of course only if it allows the financial situation of the person concerned.
Insurers' side, couples with children are considered to be customers with the lowest accident rate, and therefore their contribution payments are low.
In this case, a full-time self-participation insurance (at an amount of EUR 300) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit rating, an extended insurance is recommended, which is only used for the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is possible to complete a full-time self-interest insurance scheme (with an amount of EUR 150), or to complete an extended insurance scheme, which is only used in the case of a sufficiently high credit rating.
In the end, one must state that car insurance is a very important thing, not only because it protects the driver from possible damage to the accident, but also because it has high costs which require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
